radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild dependent atelectasis at the lung bases bilaterally; normal liver, gallbladder, spleen, adrenal glands, and pancreas; tiny renal hypodensities, atherosclerotic calcification along the abdominal aorta without aneurysmal dilatation; normal stomach and duodenum; no evidence of ileus or obstruction in small bowel; colonic diverticulosis without acute diverticulitis; stable uterine fibroid; no free fluid or free air in the pelvis; stable Grade 1 anterolisthesis of L4 on L5; bones are demineralized.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Stable appearance of tiny renal hypodensities and uterine calcified fibroid compared to prior study.
